edu.uidaho.junicon.interpreter.parser

Class AbstractParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.uidaho.junicon.grammars.common.AbstractPreprocessor
      • edu.uidaho.junicon.interpreter.parser.AbstractParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IPreprocessor, IParser, Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ParserFromGrammar, ParserFromPreprocessor

    public class AbstractParser
extends AbstractPreprocessor
implements IParser, Cloneable
    AbstractParser encapsulates common features of parsers including buffering input lines to parse and caching literals.

        public void setPreprocessor(IParser preprocessor)
        Description copied from interface: IParser
        Sets the preprocessor for this parser. The preprocessor is recursively invoked by getParseUnit() and addTextToParse(). The preprocessor should preserve lines, i.e., it can fuse lines together but not break apart lines into smaller statements.

      • getParseUnit

        public final String getParseUnit(String inputLine,
                                 ILineContext context)
                          throws ParseException
        Description copied from interface: IParser
        Obtains a parsible unit from the history of lines in the input stream. If a preprocessor has been set, this is used to first process the input line using its getParseUnit. The result is added to a history of preprocessed input lines. The next parsible unit, i.e. a complete statement, is then obtained from the preprocessed input history.
        Specified by:
        getParseUnit in interface IParser
        Parameters:
        inputLine - a line of source input, without the line separator (e.g., carriage return), to add to the input line history.
        context - input line context, passed to the preprocessor and carried through into the input history.
        Returns:
        parse unit, if the input line history has a parsible unit; null otherwise.
        Throws:
        ParseException
